WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:06.625
Hey, good morning family. Praise the Lord. Easter weekend, my favorite time of the year.

00:00:06.626 --> 00:00:09.648
Well, praise the Lord, I'm excited. It's time to be grateful.

00:00:09.649 --> 00:00:18.257
It's time to be thankful for all that Jesus has done for every single one of us. It's a time to reflect.

00:00:18.258 --> 00:00:41.336
I always just sit and watch my kids and the church things that we go to, and it makes me go inward and think about all that Jesus did—all his suffering, all that he did to break the chains of bondage off of our lives so that we could walk free.

00:00:41.337 --> 00:00:51.519
You know, I bring out this video. I've brought out a lot of videos the last couple of days that I've already brought out before, and I usually do it once a year.

00:00:51.520 --> 00:01:00.824
These are the experiences that I've had with the Lord that have changed me, and they're too good just to let get buried in the algorithm.

00:01:00.825 --> 00:01:04.356
They get weighed down at the bottom of the feed and people forget about them.

00:01:04.357 --> 00:01:22.367
So Braden, Diana, and I bring those videos out again because we believe there's life still in those videos, in that experience that I had with the Lord—that word that the Lord gave to tell you all about his coming and where the tribulation was.

00:01:22.368 --> 00:01:36.508
And now this one is about his crucifixion. I was sitting on the side of my bed one night and I was asking the Lord because one of the people of the church called and said, "Brandon, I've been suffering with arthritis for years.

00:01:36.509 --> 00:01:41.753
My hands are crippled up. I can't move my hands. I've been in so much pain.

00:01:41.754 --> 00:01:48.173
How come you think I've been a preacher?"He told me all the things that he had done and how he's still suffering.

00:01:48.174 --> 00:01:53.210
And so I thought, "I don't know. I'm overcoming stuff myself.

00:01:53.211 --> 00:02:10.436
My daughter's overcoming, and I've been standing in faith."And I told him all my sob story, you know, after you tell your sob stories of everything you go through and you listen to each other, but it still didn't fix the problem because you still are overcoming what you're overcoming.

00:02:10.437 --> 00:02:20.280
So I sat on the side of the bed and I said, "Lord, would you please explain to me why all the body of Christ is not healed? Why are we not experiencing the glory?

00:02:20.281 --> 00:02:36.411
Why have we not seen the manifestation of what we're believing for?"So I just went to sleep and all of a sudden, in that sleeping time, I had a dream.

00:02:36.412 --> 00:02:44.314
Now you know when you have a dream that is just an over-the-top dream, where you can smell things?

00:02:44.315 --> 00:02:52.496
This was like I was out of my body in my dream. This was such a supernatural dream that it was real.

00:02:52.498 --> 00:02:59.264
All of a sudden, I was standing in this courtyard. It was hot outside, probably about 80 degrees.

00:02:59.265 --> 00:03:02.635
I could actually feel the temperature. I could feel the sun hitting me.

00:03:02.636 --> 00:03:08.038
You know, whenever you're standing out there and there's no breeze? In the dream, I could feel how hot it was.

00:03:08.039 --> 00:03:13.493
And I looked around me and all of a sudden to my right hand, Jesus was standing there.

00:03:13.494 --> 00:03:23.889
And then I realized where I was. I was taken back in time and I was at the crucifixion because I could see Jesus.

00:03:23.890 --> 00:03:33.421
The Jesus that I was seeing had oily skin. He had his shirt off. His skin was dirty looking.

00:03:33.422 --> 00:03:40.940
He looked like he had dirt on him and he was being led to the whipping post.

00:03:40.941 --> 00:03:50.152
They took his hands, ladies and gentlemen, and they put them in shackles and they tied him to a whipping post in front of my face.

00:03:50.153 --> 00:03:59.057
And I could see the stanchion right here with this metal-looking hoop.

00:03:59.058 --> 00:04:07.052
And they put his hands and latched his hands on that hoop-looking thing. They put his hands up there like that.

00:04:07.053 --> 00:04:13.432
And there was a man that was dressed in solid black over on his right hand.

00:04:13.433 --> 00:04:25.039
He was probably about 300 pounds. He was a big guy, bigger than me. This man was big, and his body structure was big.

00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:40.559
His shoulders were big, but he was bald-headed with a shaved head. And on his left side was a man in Roman garb.

00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:48.429
He had a Roman helmet on, a Roman outfit on—the leather-looking outfit.

00:04:48.430 --> 00:04:59.471
It was all just like you see in Roman times. Both men had the cat-o'-nine-tails in their hands.

00:04:59.472 --> 00:05:05.968
And I saw the one man take... well, first I saw them pull his beard.

00:05:05.969 --> 00:05:11.492
I saw them rip out his beard. They were punching Jesus in the face.

00:05:11.493 --> 00:05:20.013
I could see Jesus's head bounce around as they were just beating him in the face and punching him. They were ripping his beard out of his face.

00:05:20.014 --> 00:05:27.758
They were pushing on the crown of thorns on his head because he had a crown of thorns on his head as he was there.

00:05:27.759 --> 00:05:39.296
His skin looked like it had been welped up. He looked like he had been beaten, and his back already looked bruised from somebody beating on him.

00:05:39.296 --> 00:05:48.518
His body already looked like it was—you know, whenever you see skin that was already like you were beaten with sticks?

00:05:48.519 --> 00:05:56.003
He looked like he had purple burst blood vessels that were already popped all over his back.

00:05:56.004 --> 00:06:08.031
He looked like someone who had been in a bad fight and had lost, totally purple from his body being beaten through his olive skin.

00:06:08.032 --> 00:06:15.722
And you could see the glistening on his back that looked like oil from the sweat from how hot it was outside.

00:06:15.723 --> 00:06:22.274
It was about 80 or 85 degrees, but you could see the oils from his skin.

00:06:22.275 --> 00:06:31.045
And I just remember looking at his body and I saw him being lifted up like this, above his head.

00:06:31.046 --> 00:06:41.620
And I saw his bruises all over his body and his face, and he had blood from where the beard was being ripped out of his face.

00:06:41.621 --> 00:06:51.839
There was blood dripping and it looked like what you would look like if you had hair ripped out of your head. And I could see the thorns, like I said.

00:06:51.840 --> 00:07:01.623
So these men were taking the thorns and they were pushing them on his head more because they had things on their hands, so it wasn't hurting them, but it was hurting Jesus.

00:07:01.624 --> 00:07:24.336
And I could see he was in tremendous pain. As I stood there with Jesus on this side in his glorified body, I could see him and he was watching on, and we were looking at him being whipped.

00:07:24.337 --> 00:07:34.087
And I saw the one man in the black outfit take that cat-o'-nine-tails and he went and he whipped him.

00:07:34.088 --> 00:07:40.816
And whenever he did, I saw flesh stripped off of his body like it was just big chunks.

00:07:40.817 --> 00:07:50.343
It was not just like a little bitty scratch. Ladies and gentlemen, what I saw before me was horrific.

00:07:50.344 --> 00:07:56.703
And all that came off of his body and it just scratched him deep to the bones.

00:07:56.704 --> 00:08:02.731
Then they took the other man and he took that other side and they whipped him again on this side.

00:08:02.732 --> 00:08:08.997
And as one was whipping this side, the other... and they would take turns, and each one would whip.

00:08:08.998 --> 00:08:18.658
It wasn't a break. One would whip, then the other, to the point where his flesh was dripping off of his body.

00:08:18.659 --> 00:08:32.951
Every time he was being hit, it was like he was being moved and he was screaming in agony.

00:08:32.952 --> 00:08:40.816
All I could do while I was standing there was say, "Stop! You've got to stop!"but nobody could hear me.

00:08:40.817 --> 00:08:48.432
I said, "Oh, God, they've got to stop!"because I could see his body in the pain that he was feeling.

00:08:48.433 --> 00:09:13.599
Because his arms were above his head, it was going around his chest and it was taking his skin off of his body in chunks—not just a little bit, but deep, deep wounds were just being lashed and scraped and ripped out of his body as he was taking all of the stripes for us.

00:09:13.600 --> 00:09:18.559
Blood was dripping down him and he was just in a pool of blood all around him.

00:09:18.560 --> 00:09:33.283
And Jesus said this to me: "What part of 'By my stripes you are healed'do you not understand?"He was pointing at himself.

00:09:33.284 --> 00:09:40.471
He said, "I took all that on the cross for you. I took all sickness, all disease, everything for you.

00:09:40.472 --> 00:09:55.608
And I said in my word, 'By my stripes you are healed.'"He said, "Brandon, I want to tell you something.

00:09:55.609 --> 00:10:12.537
The same way you believe that you're saved is the same way you believe for your healing."He said, "Brandon, if anybody was to tell you that you were not saved, you would fight them, wouldn't you?

